016package org.lifstools.jmzqc;
017
018import com.fasterxml.jackson.annotation.*;
019import java.time.OffsetDateTime;
020import java.util.Collections;
021import java.util.List;
022import java.util.Objects;
023import java.util.stream.Collectors;
024
025/**
026 * Root element of an mzQC file.
027 */
028public class MzQC {
029
030    private String contactAddress;
031    private String contactName;
032    private List<ControlledVocabulary> controlledVocabularies = Collections.emptyList();
033    private OffsetDateTime creationDate;
034    private String description;
035    private List<BaseQuality> runQualities = Collections.emptyList();
036    private List<BaseQuality> setQualities = Collections.emptyList();
037    private String version;
038
039    public MzQC() {
040    }
041
042    public MzQC(String contactAddress, String contactName, List<ControlledVocabulary> controlledVocabularies, OffsetDateTime creationDate, String description, List<BaseQuality> runQualities, List<BaseQuality> setQualities, String version) {
043        this.contactAddress = contactAddress;
044        this.contactName = contactName;
045        this.controlledVocabularies = controlledVocabularies;
046        this.creationDate = creationDate;
047        this.description = description;
048        this.runQualities = runQualities;
049        this.setQualities = setQualities;
050        this.version = version;
051    }
052
053    public String getContactAddress() {
054        return contactAddress;
055    }
056
057    public void setContactAddress(String contactAddress) {
058        this.contactAddress = contactAddress;
059    }
060
061    public String getContactName() {
062        return contactName;
063    }
064
065    public void setContactName(String contactName) {
066        this.contactName = contactName;
067    }
068
069    public List<ControlledVocabulary> getControlledVocabularies() {
070        return controlledVocabularies;
071    }
072
073    public void setControlledVocabularies(List<ControlledVocabulary> controlledVocabularies) {
074        this.controlledVocabularies = controlledVocabularies;
075    }
076
077    public OffsetDateTime getCreationDate() {
078        return creationDate;
079    }
080
081    public void setCreationDate(OffsetDateTime creationDate) {
082        this.creationDate = creationDate;
083    }
084
085    public String getDescription() {
086        return description;
087    }
088
089    public void setDescription(String description) {
090        this.description = description;
091    }
092
093    public List<BaseQuality> getRunQualities() {
094        return runQualities;
095    }
096
097    public void setRunQualities(List<BaseQuality> runQualities) {
098        this.runQualities = runQualities;
099    }
100
101    public List<BaseQuality> getSetQualities() {
102        return setQualities;
103    }
104
105    public void setSetQualities(List<BaseQuality> setQualities) {
106        this.setQualities = setQualities;
107    }
108
109    public String getVersion() {
110        return version;
111    }
112
113    public void setVersion(String version) {
114        this.version = version;
115    }
116
117    @Override
118    public int hashCode() {
119        int hash = 7;
120        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.contactAddress);
121        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.contactName);
122        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.controlledVocabularies);
123        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.creationDate);
124        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.description);
125        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.runQualities);
126        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.setQualities);
127        hash = 47 * hash + Objects.hashCode(this.version);
128        return hash;
129    }
130
131    @Override
132    public boolean equals(Object obj) {
133        if (this == obj) {
134            return true;
135        }
136        if (obj == null) {
137            return false;
138        }
139        if (getClass() != obj.getClass()) {
140            return false;
141        }
142        final MzQC other = (MzQC) obj;
143        if (!Objects.equals(this.contactAddress, other.contactAddress)) {
144            return false;
145        }
146        if (!Objects.equals(this.contactName, other.contactName)) {
147            return false;
148        }
149        if (!Objects.equals(this.description, other.description)) {
150            return false;
151        }
152        if (!Objects.equals(this.version, other.version)) {
153            return false;
154        }
155        if (!Objects.equals(this.controlledVocabularies, other.controlledVocabularies)) {
156            return false;
157        }
158        if (!Objects.equals(this.creationDate, other.creationDate)) {
159            return false;
160        }
161        if (!Objects.equals(this.runQualities, other.runQualities)) {
162            return false;
163        }
164        return Objects.equals(this.setQualities, other.setQualities);
165    }
166
167    /**
168     * Returns a reference to the internal list of quality metrics for the given
169     * run. Modifications are reflected in the object graph.
170     *
171     * @param index the zero-based array index of a run.
172     * @return the underlying list of qc metrics
173     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if arguments are invalid
174     */
175    @JsonIgnore
176    public List<QualityMetric> getRunQualityMetrics(int index) {
177        if (index >= 0 && index < getRunQualities().size()) {
178            return getRunQualities().get(index).getQualityMetrics();
179        }
180        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Can not access run " + index);
181    }
182
183    /**
184     * Returns a reference to the internal list of quality metrics for the given
185     * run. Modifications are reflected in the object graph.
186     *
187     * @param index the zero-based array index of a run.
188     * @param accession the cv accession for qc metrics to return
189     * @return the underlying list of qc metrics, filtered for accession
190     * @throws IllegalArgumentException if arguments are invalid
191     */
192    @JsonIgnore
193    public List<QualityMetric> getRunQualityMetricsByAccession(int index, String accession) {
194        if (index >= 0 && index < getRunQualities().size()) {
195            return getRunQualities().get(index).getQualityMetrics().stream().filter((qm) -> {
196                return accession.equals(qm.getAccession());
197            }).collect(Collectors.toList());
198        }
199        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Can not access run " + index);
200    }
201}
